RE: Peter Schafer&#039;s quote in &quot;The Mirror of His Beauty&quot; (2002) p. 36.: &quot;Herself unchanging ~ she makes all things new&quot; ~
&quot;Herself unchanging ~ she makes all things new&quot; is actually from &quot;Sophia of the Bible&quot; by Aurora Terrenus. (1986) (p. 64)
This is my own interpretation of The Wisdom of Solomon 7:27-28, which reads: &quot;Though she is but one, she can do all things and while remaining in herself, she renews all things.&quot;
